message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Benin, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you have the time, walking can be a good option. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km on foot.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a faster and more convenient option. It will take you around 5-7 minutes to reach the grocery store.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability of public transportation in your area, you can check if there are buses or minibusses that pass by or near the grocery store. You can inquire about the nearest bus stop and take a bus to reach your destination.

4. Taxi or Motorcycle Taxi: Taxis and motorcycle taxis (known as "zemidjans" in Benin) are a common mode of transportation. You can easily find a taxi or motorcycle taxi nearby and negotiate a fare to take you to the grocery store.

Remember to consider factors such as safety, convenience, and cost when choosing your mode of transportation.
